fixed.key_facts:
Equation of a parabola: y = ax² + bx + c;
Equation of a straight line: ax + by + c = 0;
Intersection of two lines: solve simultaneous linear equations;
Area of a region bounded by two curves: ∫(y₂-y₁) dx, where y₁ and y₂ are the bounding curves.

Arithmetic sequence formula: an = a1 + (n-1)d; 
Matrix multiplication rule;
Determinant of a 3x3 matrix formula: |A| = a11(a22a33 - a23a32) - a12(a21a33 - a23a31) + a13(a21a32 - a22a31);
Binomial theorem: (a+b)^n = Σ(nCr * a^(n-r) * b^r), r = 0 to n;
Sum of an arithmetic sequence formula: Sn = (n/2)(a1 + an).

Polynomial degree formula: degree(P(x)) ≥ number of roots of P''(x) + 1; 
Inflection point condition: P''(x) = 0;
Derivative formulas: P'(x), P''(x);
Trigonometry: tan(60°) = √3;
Fundamental Theorem of Calculus: ∫₀¹ P(x) dx = P(1) - P(0).

Combinatorics and Permutations:
- Permutation formula: P(n,r) = n! / (n-r)!;
- Combination formula: C(n,r) = n! / (r!(n-r)!);
- Fundamental Counting Principle.

Divisibility Rules:
- Divisibility by 7: (2x + 5y) % 7 = 0.

Modular Arithmetic:
- Modulus operation (remainder on division);
- Congruence relation: a ≡ b (mod n) if n|(a-b).

Symmetry property of periodic functions: f(2-x) = f(2+x); f(4-x) = f(4+x); Period: T = 4;
Fundamental Theorem of Calculus: ∫(a to b) f(x) dx = F(b) - F(a), where F'(x) = f(x);
Linearity of Definite Integrals: ∫(a to b) k f(x) dx = k ∫(a to b) f(x) dx.
